DEMO

An RPC mechanism for a personnel file application.

Files:
- personnel.mpl:        The protocol specification
- pers_server.c:        Server main
- pers_handlers.{c,h}:  Server side handlers
- pers_db.{c,h}:        Server side database impementation
- pers_cc_api.cc:       Client side C++ api demo main
- pers_cli.c:           Client side command line interface main
                        (features command completion, history
                        and help function)
- pers_test.exp:        A script demonstrating some of the
                        test possibilities

  The rest are either generated by the compiler (after running make)
  or support library files.


Build:

    make

    - This will run the compiler and compile the programs
      (pers_server, pers_cli and pers_cc_api).

    make check

    - This will generate tcl code and run a small test of the server

    make memcheck

    - This will run the above test in valgrind (logs in directory ./memcheck/)
      (requires valgrind)

    make doc

    - This will generate html documentation of the protocol in
      subdirectory ./personnel/
      (requires latex and latex2html)

Run:

    Make named pipes:

        mknod toserver p
        mknod fromserver p

    Start the server in terminal window:

        ./pers_server -i toserver -o fromserver

    Start a client in an other terminal window:

        either:

            ./pers_cc_api -i fromserver -o toserver

        or:

            ./pers_cli -i fromserver -o toserver

/Per
